Yocto repositories patch

This three contains specific patches for the Yocto tree that will enable Variscite's platform DART-SD410.
Usage:
Install repo:
$ mkdir ~/bin
$ PATH=~/bin:$PATH
$ curl http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/git-repo-downloads/repo > ~/bin/repo
$ chmod a+x ~/bin/repo

Download sources:
$ mkdir -p ~/sd410-yocto/pyro
$ cd  ~/sd410-yocto/pyro
$ repo init -u https://github.com/96boards/oe-rpb-manifest.git -b pyro
$ repo sync -j10

Download the meta-qcom patch:
$ git clone https://github.com/varigit/DART-SD410-repo-patch.git
$ cd DART-SD410-repo-patch
$ git checkout -b yocto/pyro remotes/origin/yocto/pyro

Apply the patch to meta-qcom layer.
$ cd ../layers/meta-qcom
$ git am ../../DART-SD410-repo-patch/meta-qcom/0001-dart-sd410-Variscite-DART-SD410-platform-support-add.patch

If you want to use HDMI screen apply the HDMI patch:
$ git apply ../../DART-SD410-repo-patch/meta-qcom/HDMI_Enable_patch.diff

Setup environment:
$ source setup-environment
choose dart-sd410 platform
select distribution

Build the image:
$ bitbake rpb-console-image rpb-desktop-image
	
To burn the images, burn the RescueImages first and 
then change to the new built one the rootfs and boot image.

After the first boot the SOM will recognize wrong partition size.
The rootfs partition will be very small.
